The United States government has retracted its previous decision to withdraw from the World Health Organization (WHO). In a letter addressed to the Secretary-General of the United Nations, Joseph R. Biden Jr., the President of the United States, stated that the country intends to remain a member of the WHO. The letter emphasizes the crucial role of the WHO in combating the COVID-19 pandemic and other global health threats. The United States pledges to continue actively participating in efforts to address these challenges and promote global health security.